Delicious food! I've eaten in the diner for breakfast, and their pancakes (banana) were the bomb! Boyfriend had the french toast, and it was delicous. Eggs, sausages, bacon, and corned beef hash was very good. We also had the hot chocolate with whipped cream and also an egg cream, which was great. The diner itself isn't large, but seemed to be very busy. I plan to come back and try their oreganata, and fra diavolo. I ordered from UberEats from them, and am so surprised by this mushroom stuffed crab.. it is so tasty. Eggplant parmesan is huge, breaded, and tasty. Will update when I try more dishes. This place is a new favorite for me. I heard diners were dying out, but I hope this one doesn't-- mind you, this isn't a romantic place to take your date (unless they're cool). It's definitely a busy place where families eat. I don't mind that at all, especially since the food won me over.
